00:02:53.310 --> 00:02:56.700
What we find is that if we look
at the motion of this thing

00:02:56.700 --> 00:03:00.090
as a function of the proper
time of that in-falling body,

00:03:00.090 --> 00:03:04.500
it crosses 2GM in
finite proper time.

00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:07.530
And shortly afterwards,
again, in finite proper time,

00:03:07.530 --> 00:03:10.590
it reaches the r equals
0 tidal singularity.

00:03:10.590 --> 00:03:14.565
If I look at that same
motion as a function

00:03:14.565 --> 00:03:17.300
of the coordinate
time t, it never

00:03:17.300 --> 00:03:22.620
even reaches, never even
reaches r equals 2GM.

00:03:22.620 --> 00:03:24.180
We found a solution,
what you can

00:03:24.180 --> 00:03:26.010
see in notes that
I've put online

00:03:26.010 --> 00:03:29.263
and that are presented
