approaches r equals 2GM,

00:03:34.350 --> 00:03:39.210
only reaching that radius in
the t goes to infinity limit.

00:03:39.210 --> 00:03:41.720
These are two starkly
different pictures

00:03:41.720 --> 00:03:43.790
of the kinematics of
this in-falling body.

00:03:43.790 --> 00:03:46.120
So the question is,
what is going on here?

00:03:46.120 --> 00:03:48.260
And as food for
thought, I reminded us

00:03:48.260 --> 00:03:51.710
that these coordinates, if
we sort of look at the way

00:03:51.710 --> 00:03:54.860
that spacetime behaves for
a very, very, very large M--

00:03:54.860 --> 00:03:56.960
Excuse me, very,
very, very large R,

00:03:56.960 --> 00:04:01.220
not M, but for a very large R,
R much, much greater than 2GM,

00:04:01.220 --> 00:04:03.830
this turns into the line
element of flat spacetime.

00:04:03.830 --> 00:04:06.530
Flat spacetime is what we
use in special relativity.

00:04:06.530 --> 00:04:08.240
And our time
coordinate there, it

00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:12.110
is designed using this
Einstein synchronization

00:04:12.110 --> 00:04:16.279
procedure, which means that
the properties of light

00:04:16.279 --> 00:04:18.350
as it propagates
through spacetime

00:04:18.350 --> 00:04:21.740
are built into the
coordinate system.

00:04:21.740 --> 00:04:23.218
So that suggests
what we might want

00:04:23.218 --> 00:04:25.760
to start doing in order to try
to get some insight as to what

00:04:25.760 --> 00:04:30.260
is going on with this
weird spacetime is

00:04:30.260 --> 00:04:33.770
to think about light as it
propagates into spacetime.

00:04:33.770 --> 00:04:37.134
Let's think about what happens
to radiation as it propagates.

00:04:39.860 --> 00:04:53.480
So let's imagine as the body
falls that it emits a radio

00:04:53.480 --> 00:05:16.630
pulse with a
frequency as measured

00:05:16.630 --> 00:05:18.070
according to the in falling.

00:05:18.070 --> 00:05:19.445
Let's say there's
an observer who

00:05:19.445 --> 00:05:21.820
is falling in who's got a
little radio transmitter that's

00:05:21.820 --> 00:05:24.010
beaming this message out.

00:05:24.010 --> 00:05:27.820
And according to that observer,
this thing is emitted,

00:05:27.820 --> 00:05:30.880
the pulse has a
frequency omega--

00:05:33.520 --> 00:05:42.440
very far away, we can
describe the momentum

00:05:42.440 --> 00:05:51.680
of this radio pulse like so.

00:05:51.680 --> 00:05:58.440
Imagine the thing is propagating
out radially and very,

00:05:58.440 --> 00:06:02.510
very far away where the
spacetime is approximately

00:06:02.510 --> 00:06:03.680
flat.

00:06:03.680 --> 00:06:06.920
It's simply the
four-momentum that

00:06:06.920 --> 00:06:11.180
describes a null geodesic moving
in the radial direction, OK?

00:06:11.180 --> 00:06:14.000
Minus sign here because with the
index in the upstairs position

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:16.190
and this asymptotically
flat region,

00:06:16.190 --> 00:06:18.030
that would be the energy.

00:06:18.030 --> 00:06:20.480
So a couple of facts
to bear in mind.

00:06:27.770 --> 00:06:38.820
The energy measured by an
observer with four-velocity

00:06:38.820 --> 00:06:48.090
U is given by, let's call it
E sub U, the energy measured

00:06:48.090 --> 00:06:57.420
by observer U. This
is minus P-dot-U.

00:06:57.420 --> 00:07:02.372
We developed this in
special relativity.

00:07:02.372 --> 00:07:04.830
But remember the way that we
use the equivalence principle.

00:07:04.830 --> 00:07:06.955
We're gonna use the Einstein
equivalence principle.

00:07:06.955 --> 00:07:10.470
And any law that holds in a
freely falling frame, if I

00:07:10.470 --> 00:07:12.570
can write it in a
tensorial way that

00:07:12.570 --> 00:07:15.300
works in that freely falling
frame, it works in any frame.

00:07:15.300 --> 00:07:17.820
So this tensorial
statement holds true,

00:07:17.820 --> 00:07:20.850
even though we are now
working in the spacetime that

00:07:20.850 --> 00:07:23.640
is distinctly different
from special relativity.

00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:40.850
We also know that in a
time independent spacetime,

00:07:40.850 --> 00:07:46.470
the downstairs T component
of four momentum is constant.

00:07:53.480 --> 00:08:01.130
So what this basically means
is if I think about this radio

00:08:01.130 --> 00:08:03.290
pulse with its light
propagating out

00:08:03.290 --> 00:08:08.270
through the spacetime, the value
P0 associated with this thing's

00:08:08.270 --> 00:08:10.220
four momentum, it's
the same everywhere

00:08:10.220 --> 00:08:11.868
along its trajectory.

00:08:18.570 --> 00:08:25.620
So let's consider a
static observer sitting

00:08:25.620 --> 00:08:27.099
in the Schwarzschild spacetime.

00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:50.130
OK, I'm going to require
G-alpha-beta U-alpha

00:08:50.130 --> 00:08:52.864
U-beta to be equal to minus 1.

00:08:52.864 --> 00:08:58.730
And I will require that this
have some timelike piece,

00:08:58.730 --> 00:09:00.580
that this observer is static.

00:09:00.580 --> 00:09:03.450
So their spatial components
of their four-velocity

00:09:03.450 --> 00:09:04.880
are equal to 0.

00:09:04.880 --> 00:09:07.890
It looks like, by the way--
